718. aeq. Ion.: Several of the earlier Greek writers use the term Ionian Gulf (Ἰόνιος κόλπος) as synonymous with Adriatic. The later geographers considered the Ionian Sea as extending along the south coast of Italy, including the entrance of the Adriatic, and reaching on the one hand as far as Greece‚ on the other to Sicily. The Latin writ- ers, generally, use the term in this latter sense. See Smith, ‘ Dict. of Geog.' art. Ionium Mare. 719. glaucis: Greek γλαυκός.
